---
import Main from '../layouts/Main.astro'
import Hero from '../layouts/Hero.astro'
---

<Main title="Goals">

    <Hero title="Goals" image="/images/goals.jpeg" slot="hero">
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Building standards for zebrafish toxicology research</p>
    </Hero>

    <section class="mission">
        <div class="section-label">Our Mission</div>
        <p>The Zebrafish Atlas Phenotype Project (ZAPP) is a community driven effort focused on standardizing zebrafish toxicology data and phenotypic outcome reporting. ZAPP's success depends on active participation from the zebrafish research and toxicology community to ensure that ZAPP remains fit for purpose, sustainable, and effective in improving the integration and reuse of toxicological and phenotypic data.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="aims">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon section-icon--green">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h2>ZAPP Aims To:</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="aims-card">
            <ul>
                <li>Develop a <strong>data model</strong> and standards to report zebrafish exposure experiments and resulting phenotypes</li>
                <li>Create an <strong>annotation toolkit</strong> that enables consistent data annotation following the data model and standards. This annotation toolkit will allow standards adoption without prior knowledge of ontologies or data modeling.</li>
                <li>Build a web-based, community-curated <strong>phenotype atlas</strong> that serves as a visual reference for zebrafish phenotypes</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="workflow">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon section-icon--teal">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h2>ZAPP Workflow &amp; Data Pipeline</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="workflow-diagram">
            <img src="/images/goals-workflow.jpg" alt="ZAPP data workflow: zebrafish exposure data collection, toxicophenotype annotation using standards, submission to the Zebrafish Phenotype Atlas with FAIR data standards" />
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="deliverables">
        <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-icon section-icon--dark">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2>Key Deliverables</h2>
                <p class="section-subtitle">Our project focuses on three major deliverables that will transform zebrafish toxicology research</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="deliverable">
            <h3>Data Model and Standards for Toxicophenotype</h3>
            <p>We are creating a <a href="https://linkml.io/linkml/">LinkML</a>-based data model, based on existing toxicological data structures to support comprehensive representation of toxicological exposures, including time course, toxicants, concentrations, fish information, and phenotypic endpoints. The LinkML schema is developed with community input across multiple toxicology use cases and designed for use across organisms. More information about the data model can be found <a href="https://github.com/zappfish/zebrafish-toxicology-atlas-schema">here</a>.</p>
            <p>In addition, we improve standards to represent all data, including (but not limited to):</p>
            <ul class="callout-list">
                <li>The <a href="https://github.com/obophenotype/zebrafish-phenotype-ontology">Zebrafish Phenotype ontology</a> (ZP) — to represent zebrafish phenotypes</li>
                <li>The <a href="https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/environmental-exposure-ontology">Environment Exposure Ontology</a> (ECTO) — to represent exposure route terms</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="deliverable">
            <h3>Annotation Toolkit for Toxicophenotype</h3>
            <p>We aim to develop a community-driven toxicophenotype annotation toolkit aligned with the toxicophenotype data model to support standardized data annotation and submission to the ZAPP Atlas.</p>
            <ul class="callout-list">
                <li>Tutorials and curation guidelines will be provided to ensure consistent annotation across contributors</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="deliverable">
            <h3>Phenotype Atlas Web application</h3>
            <p>We will collect images and metadata of morphological phenotypes from toxicology studies using the toxicophenotype annotation toolkit. These data will instantiate a zebrafish phenotype atlas and provide visual standards for comparing phenotype variation across laboratories.</p>
            <ul class="callout-list">
                <li>The open source web-based phenotype atlas will support exploration and querying of exposures and phenotypes, display representative images and link to relevant external resources</li>
                <li>FAIR API access to the data will be provided for third-party resources</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="action-cards">
        <div class="action-card">
            <div class="action-card-icon">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Contribute Data</h3>
                <p>Submit your zebrafish toxicology data and phenotype observations to help build the atlas.</p>
                <a href="/events" class="action-link">Upcoming Workshops &rsaquo;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="action-card">
            <div class="action-card-icon">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/><line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Upcoming Workshops</h3>
                <p>Join our workshops to learn about data annotation standards and contribute to the community.</p>
                <a href="/events" class="action-link">View Events &rsaquo;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-band">
        <h2>Get Involved with ZAPP</h2>
        <p>Are you passionate about zebrafish research and standards? Help shape the data models, contribute annotated images and phenotype data, or help us fine-tune the annotation tools.</p>
        <a href="/get-involved" class="cta-btn">Join the Community</a>
    </section>

</Main>

<style>
    /* ── Hero subtitle ── */
    .hero-subtitle {
        color: var(--color-text-white);
        font-size: var(--font-size-body);
        margin: 0;
        opacity: 0.92;
    }

    /* ── Mission ── */
    .mission {
        padding-top: var(--space-8);
    }

    .section-label {
        font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
        padding-left: var(--space-3);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    }

    /* ── Section headers with icon ── */
    .section-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: var(--space-4);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    }

    .section-header h2,
    .section-header > div h2 {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    }

    .section-subtitle {
        font-size: var(--font-size-base);
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        margin: 0;
    }

    .section-icon {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        color: #fff;
    }

    .section-icon svg { width: 20px; height: 20px; }

    .section-icon--green { background: var(--color-accent); }
    .section-icon--teal  { background: var(--color-primary-dark); }
    .section-icon--dark  { background: var(--color-primary); }

    /* ── Aims card ── */
    .aims-card {
        background: var(--color-bg-white);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-8) var(--space-8) var(--space-12);
        box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
    }

    .aims-card ul { margin: 0; }
    .aims-card li { font-size: var(--font-size-body); line-height: var(--line-height-base); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
    .aims-card li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    /* ── Workflow diagram ── */
    .workflow-diagram {
        border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: 10px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--color-bg-white);
        padding: var(--space-6);
    }

    .workflow-diagram img {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
    }

    /* ── Deliverables ── */
    .deliverable {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
        padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .deliverable:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
        margin-bottom: 0;
        padding-bottom: 0;
    }

    .deliverable h3 {
        font-size: var(--font-size-h3);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    }

    .callout-list {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin-top: var(--space-3);
    }

    .callout-list li {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
        padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
        font-size: var(--font-size-body);
        line-height: var(--line-height-base);
        background: var(--color-bg-white);
        border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
    }

    .callout-list li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    /* ── Action cards ── */
    .action-cards {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: var(--space-6);
    }

    .action-card {
        background: var(--color-bg-white);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: var(--space-8);
        box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
        display: flex;
        gap: var(--space-4);
        align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .action-card-icon {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 36px;
        height: 36px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: var(--color-bg-base);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        color: var(--color-primary);
    }

    .action-card-icon svg { width: 18px; height: 18px; }

    .action-card h3 { font-size: var(--font-size-h3); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
    .action-card p  { font-size: var(--font-size-base); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); line-height: var(--line-height-base); }

    .action-link {
        font-size: var(--font-size-base);
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
        color: var(--color-accent);
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .action-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    /* ── CTA band (full-bleed dark section) ── */
    .cta-band {
        background: var(--color-primary-dark);
        text-align: center;
        padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-8);
        border-radius: 12px;
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .cta-band h2 { color: var(--color-text-white); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }

    .cta-band p {
        color: var(--color-white-65);
        max-width: 540px;
        margin: 0 auto var(--space-8);
    }

    .cta-btn {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-8);
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--color-text-white);
        border: 2px solid var(--color-text-white);
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
        font-size: var(--font-size-base);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
    }

    .cta-btn:hover {
        background: var(--color-text-white);
        color: var(--color-primary-dark);
    }

    /* ── Responsive ── */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .action-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
</style>
